1. How to build?
   (1) You can jus type 'make' in the directory where you find this README file.
   (2) To build a debug version with debugging symbols, type 'make DEBUG=1'.
   (3) To view more debugging information when this daemon runs, you can type
       'make UPNP_DEBUG_INFO=1'
   (4) Likewise, if you want debugging symbols as well as more debugging
       information, type 'make DEBUG=1 UPNP_DEBUG_INFO=1'

2. How to run?
   After you build the source, you can see a 'upnpd' executable in this
   directory:
   (1) Make sure there is also a 'upnpd.conf' file in the same directory.
   (2) Use 'tail -f /var/log/messages' command to see logging information.
   (3) Invoke the UPnP daemon by typing './upnpd',
   (4) Invoke the daemon by typing './upnpd -d' if you have set UPNP_DEBUG_INFO
       flag to 1 when you build the source, and want to see more debugging
       information.
   (5) To stop the daemon, type './upnpd --shutdown'.

3. Known issues: please read the 'TODO' file in this same directory.

4. For more information, please read the documents in 'doc' directory.

